{"session_id":"svc-1778206874946433344","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-08T02:21:17.282108906Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-b8bbd0a6-20260508T022039-cceaca3a","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260508T022039-cceaca3a/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260508T022039-cceaca3a/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260508T022039-cceaca3a/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260508T022039-cceaca3a/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260508T022039-cceaca3a/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Decomposition depth cap\u0026#xA;This bead is already at decomposition depth 2. Do not create another child layer; if it is still too large, reject the split with a short explanation and write no_changes_rationale.txt instead.\u0026#xA;\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-b8bbd0a6\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ehooks: make pre-push race gate explicit about CGO\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;The pre-push full-tests hook can fail before running tests because the Go race detector requires cgo, but the hook invokes `go test -race` without ensuring `CGO_ENABLED=1` or producing a clear skip when cgo is unavailable. This blocks otherwise valid tracker/agent work at push time with a host-environment error.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- lefthook.yml:545-550 defines the pre-push `full-tests` command as `go test -race -cover ./...` under `cli/`.\u0026#xA;- Recent push attempts failed with `go: -race requires cgo; enable cgo by setting CGO_ENABLED=1` because the hook inherited an environment with cgo disabled.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/server/perf/perf_test.go:32-37 already accounts for race builds by disabling perf percentile budgets under `-race`, so the intended gate is to run the race build, not to fail before test startup.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Make the pre-push full-tests hook explicitly set `CGO_ENABLED=1` before `go test -race -cover ./...` on platforms where the Go toolchain supports cgo.\u0026#xA;- If cgo is genuinely unavailable, fail with an actionable message or skip only the race flag while still running a non-race full package gate. Pick one policy and document it in the hook/test so operators understand the behavior.\u0026#xA;- Add a regression test that parses lefthook.yml and proves the full-tests command cannot regress to a bare `go test -race` without CGO handling.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not weaken the pre-commit hook or merge-policy hook.\u0026#xA;- Do not change package-level race/perf test behavior except as required to make the hook invoke the intended gate.\u0026#xA;- Do not make local pushes depend on network access.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PARENT + DEPS\u0026#xA;Parent: ddx-a9d130d0. No deps.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestLefthookPrePushFullTestsSetsCGOForRace verifies the pre-push full-tests command either exports/sets `CGO_ENABLED=1` for `go test -race` or routes through a wrapper with equivalent CGO handling.\u0026#xA;2. TestLefthookPrePushFullTestsHasActionableCGOUnavailablePath verifies the hook has a clear behavior when cgo is unavailable, either an actionable failure or documented non-race fallback.\u0026#xA;3. `lefthook run pre-push --commands full-tests` no longer fails with `go: -race requires cgo` on a host whose Go toolchain supports cgo.\u0026#xA;4. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... -run \u0026#34;TestLefthookPrePushFullTests\u0026#34; -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;5. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:hooks, area:test, kind:bug, reliability, prevention, pre-push\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-a9d130d0\" base-rev=\"dcab8cbc22f05d02b881095eb7767906e819345d\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260508T022039-cceaca3a\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260508T022039-cceaca3a","base_rev":"dcab8cbc22f05d02b881095eb7767906e819345d","bead_id":"ddx-b8bbd0a6","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260508T022039-cceaca3a","correlation_id":"ddx-b8bbd0a6:20260508T022039-cceaca3a","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260508T022039-cceaca3a/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"cc718699efc63e1ebc76aade258149488be24e087b3c016bfc0f767560da7f4e","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-fb840889","worker_id":""}}}
